Activity and Ad Interest Analysis

Introduction

This report explores the relationship between YouTube ad experiences and user interest. Data was collected via a short survey asking participants about ad frequency, types, and their level of interest.

Plot 1: Number of entries over time

This line chart shows the number of survey entries recorded each day. The x-axis represents the date, and the y-axis shows the count of entries per day. The chart visualizes how participant activity varied over time, highlighting trends such as spikes in data collection or periods of low engagement

Number of entries plot

Plot 2: Activity Type and Ad Engagement

Here, we categorize users by their responses and count how often each ad interest type appeared. This helps identify which activities are linked with more positive ad engagement.

Ad interest Plot

Plot 3: Ad Description Complexity Over Time

This scatter plot displays the 30 most detailed responses to the question ‘What type of ads did you see?’. The x-axis shows the date and time each response was submitted, and the y-axis represents the estimated word count of each response, calculated by counting spaces plus one. Each point represents a single entry, highlighting when participants gave longer and more complex answers.”

Word count plot

Conclusion

From this exploration, it’s evident that most ads fail to capture user interest, though certain activity types might correspond with more engaged reactions. Understanding when and why users find ads interesting can help advertisers create more compelling and relevant content.
